ciscoSvcInterfaceMIB.name: ciscoSvcInterfaceMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoSvcInterfaceMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553 -NETS E-mail: cs-san@cisco.com
ciscoSvcInterfaceMIB.description: MIB module for displaying and configuring SVC (SAN Volume Controller) related features in the Storage Area Network (SAN) switches. SVC is the SAN Volume Controller that implements the specialized virtualization and caching features for storage attached to a SAN.

NportType.name: NportType
NportType.description: Type of the virtual N-port. The types are 1 = Initiator 2 = Target 3 = Mgmt

csiNportTable.name: csiNportTable
csiNportTable.description: A table that lets the user configure and monitor the virtual N-ports. A virtual N-port is a logical entity within an SVC line card that simulates a real Fibre Channel N-port.

csiNportEntry.name: csiNportEntry
csiNportEntry.description: An entry in the csiNportTable, that describes a virtual N-port. Each virtual N-port is identified by the ifIndex of the SVC interface on the SVC line card, the type of N-port and the VSAN id of the VSAN it belongs to. Each virtual N-port also has a Fibre Channel Identifier, operational state and a WWN (Worldwide Name).

csiNportIfIndex.name: csiNportIfIndex
csiNportIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the SVC interface to which this Nport belongs to. A SVC interface is a FC interface that implements virtualization and caching. Note that the ifType of this interface is fiberChannel (56).

csiNportType.name: csiNportType
csiNportType.description: The type of this N-port. There are 3 types of Nport - initiator - Initiates communication with SCSI (Small Computer Systems Interface) targets. target - Responds to the communication from the FC-SCSI initiators. mgmt - Communicates with other SVC interfaces.

csiNportVsanId.name: csiNportVsanId
csiNportVsanId.description: The VSAN identifier of the virtual N-port.

csiNportPwwn.name: csiNportPwwn
csiNportPwwn.description: The WWN (Worldwide Name) of the virtual N-port.

csiNportFcid.name: csiNportFcid
csiNportFcid.description: Fibre Channel Identifier of the virtual N-port.

csiNportState.name: csiNportState
csiNportState.description: The operational state of the virtual N-port.

csiNportDownReason.name: csiNportDownReason
csiNportDownReason.description: If the state of the N-port is 'down' as depicted by the instance of csiNportState, this objects denotes the reason why this N-port is 'down'. When the N-port is 'up' the value returned by this object is 'none'. adminDown - The user has configured the SVC interface that contains this N-port as down. ifSoftwareDown - Virtualization software is down. lineCardSwDown - Line card software is down. vsanDown - The VSAN that this N-port belongs to (instance of csiNportVsanId), is down. inRemovalState - The SVC interface that this N-port belongs to, is in the process of going down. ifHardwareDown - The line card hardware is down. uninitialized - Port is being initialized.

csiSessionTable.name: csiSessionTable
csiSessionTable.description: A table of SVC sessions. A SVC session is a FC session between a virtual N-port and any other N-port within a FC fabric.

csiSessionEntry.name: csiSessionEntry
csiSessionEntry.description: An entry in the csiSessionTable. An entry in the session table is identified by a virtual N-port and a session Identifier. Each N-port is identified by the ifIndex, Nport type and the VSAN id as described above in the csiNportEntry. The combination of the N-port and the sessionId uniquely identifies a session. Each session has the local N-port's WWN, remote N-port's WWN and remote node's WWN as well as remote N-port's FcId.

csiSessionIfIndex.name: csiSessionIfIndex
csiSessionIfIndex.description: The ifIndex of the SVC interface to which this N-port belongs to.

csiSessionType.name: csiSessionType
csiSessionType.description: The type of the N-port for this session.

csiSessionVsanId.name: csiSessionVsanId
csiSessionVsanId.description: The VSAN identifier of the N-port for this session.

csiSessionId.name: csiSessionId
csiSessionId.description: The session identifier of this session.

csiSessionNportPwwn.name: csiSessionNportPwwn
csiSessionNportPwwn.description: The WWN of the N-port that belongs to this session.

csiSessionPeerPwwn.name: csiSessionPeerPwwn
csiSessionPeerPwwn.description: The WWN of the remote N-port for this session.

csiSessionPeerNwwn.name: csiSessionPeerNwwn
csiSessionPeerNwwn.description: The WWN of the remote node for this session.

csiSessionPeerFcid.name: csiSessionPeerFcid
csiSessionPeerFcid.description: Fibre Channel Identifier of the remote port for this session.

csiInterfaceStatsTable.name: csiInterfaceStatsTable
csiInterfaceStatsTable.description: A table that lists various statistics for each SVC interface.

csiInterfaceStatsEntry.name: csiInterfaceStatsEntry
csiInterfaceStatsEntry.description: An entry in the csiInterfaceStatsTable, indexed by the N-port ifIndex and containing interface statistics such as the input and output frames, bytes and rates.

csiInterfaceInFrames.name: csiInterfaceInFrames
csiInterfaceInFrames.description: Number of incoming frames on this interface.

csiInterfaceInFrameRate.name: csiInterfaceInFrameRate
csiInterfaceInFrameRate.description: Number of incoming frames per second on this interface.

csiInterfaceInBytes.name: csiInterfaceInBytes

csiInterfaceInBytesRate.name: csiInterfaceInBytesRate

csiInterfaceOutBytesRate.name: csiInterfaceOutBytesRate
csiInterfaceOutBytesRate.description: Number of outgoing bytes per second on this interface.

csiNportSessions.description: Number of pen sessions on this virtual N-port.

csiNportInFrames.name: csiNportInFrames

csiNportOutBytes.name: csiNportOutBytes

csiSessionOutFCPStatus.description: Number of outgoing FCP Status frames in this session.

csiSessionOutFCPDataBytes.name: csiSessionOutFCPDataBytes
csiSessionOutFCPDataBytes.description: Number of outgoing FCP Data bytes in this session.

csiSessionOutFCPOverRuns.name: csiSessionOutFCPOverRuns
csiSessionOutFCPOverRuns.description: Number of outgoing FCP Overrun frames in this session.

csiSessionOutFCPUnderRuns.name: csiSessionOutFCPUnderRuns

csiInterfaceNwwnTable.name: csiInterfaceNwwnTable
csiInterfaceNwwnTable.description: A table that lists Nwwn for SVC interfaces.

csiInterfaceNwwnEntry.name: csiInterfaceNwwnEntry
csiInterfaceNwwnEntry.description: An entry in the csiInterfaceNwwnTable, indexed by the N-port ifIndex and containing interface Nwwn and a description of the cause if that interface is down.

csiInterfaceOperStateCause.name: csiInterfaceOperStateCause
csiInterfaceOperStateCause.description: A description of the cause that the interface is down.

csiSlotNumber.name: csiSlotNumber
csiSlotNumber.description: Slot Number of the slot from where the notification is being generated.

csiPortNumber.name: csiPortNumber
csiPortNumber.description: Port Number of the port from where the notification is being generated.

csiObjName.name: csiObjName
csiObjName.description: User configured name of an object. e.g. vDisk1, where the user has named the virtual disk 1 as vDisk1.

csiErrorText.name: csiErrorText
csiErrorText.description: Full text string describing the Error.

csiMachineType.name: csiMachineType
csiMachineType.description: Machine Type in which the SVC software is running. This could be the vendor product identifier. e.g MDS9000

csiCardSerialNo.name: csiCardSerialNo
csiCardSerialNo.description: The serial number of the card from where the notification is being generated.

csiSwitchName.name: csiSwitchName
csiSwitchName.description: The user configured name of the switch that is running the SVC software.

csiClusterName.name: csiClusterName
csiClusterName.description: The user configured name of the cluster.

csiNodeName.name: csiNodeName
csiNodeName.description: The user configured name of the SVC node.

csiErrorTrap.name: csiErrorTrap
csiErrorTrap.description: SVC error trap. The objects within this trap convey the information about things such as the port number, slot number machine type etc for which the error occurred. This notification will be generated when there is an error condition in any of the SVC operations.

csiWarningTrap.name: csiWarningTrap
csiWarningTrap.description: SVC warning trap The objects within this trap convey the information about things such as the port number, slot number machine type etc for which the error occurred. This notification will be generated when there is an warning condition in any of the SVC operations.

csiInformationTrap.name: csiInformationTrap
csiInformationTrap.description: SVC information trap The objects within this trap convey the information about things such as the port number, slot number machine type etc for which the information needs to be conveyed. This notification will be generated when there is an information needs to be conveyed in any of the SVC operations.
